4. The Honourable Warden of All Souls Depos'd, That I
ſaid before the Delegates, in theſe, or ſuch like Words to this effect;
If I had ſaid the Words above mention'd, I had my Author
for them; and again, That when I was ask'd by one of the Doctors,
Whether I would clear my ſelf upon Oath, I anſwer'd, I
wou'd not.

Thus much then for the Words as they are Actionable, and
relate my Expulſion: come I to the Second thing propoſed,
Namely;
